article.description: Carl Pierre had 21 points as UMass topped VCU 60-52 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Pierre scores 21 to lift UMass past VCU 60-52
article.linkText: Pierre scores 21 to lift UMass past VCU 60-52
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- Carl Pierre had 21 points as UMass topped VCU 60-52 on Wednesday night. Tre Mitchell had 19 points, 15 rebounds and three blocks for UMass (13-15, 7-8 Atlantic 10 Conference). Sean East II added 10 points and six assists. VCU scored 19 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Marcus Santos-Silva had 14 points, 11 rebounds and three blocks for the Rams (17-11, 7-8), who have now lost five games in a row. De'Riante Jenkins added 13 points and seven rebounds. UMass matches up against Richmond on the road on Saturday. VCU matches up against George Washington at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
